occurrenceRemarks.x: Cow pasture, open lush meadow. The cows were in the pasture south of the road to the ranch. The northeast side of the northern meadow had more recent cow activity than the northwestern side. Meadow/pasture associates had: Salix lasiolepis, S. laevigata (both heavily browsed, more so the former, because of shrubby habit). Pinus ponderosa (around the dry margins of meadow). Artemisia tridentata, A. ludoviciana, Eriogonum fasciculatum, Carex praegracilis, Juncus balticus, J. bufonius, Poa pratensis, Elymus triticoides, Taraxacum officinale, Achillea millefolium, Symphyotrichum sp., Solidago velutina californica, Cirsium vulgare, C. scariosum citrinum, Sidalcea sp., Verbascum thapsus, Ranunculus californicus, R. sceleratus, Veronica anagallis-aquatica, Lotus corniculatus, Melilotus indicus, Potentilla gracilis fastigiata, and Rumex salicifolius. Growing in dry areas.
locality.x: San Bernardino National ForestPeninsular Ranges; San Jacinto Mountains region: Garner Cattle Company (Garner Ranch), east of Lake Hemet, and Highway 74. West of the ranch's buildings. North of the road to the buildings, and south of the old landing strip.; Idyllwild Quad.Started near 33.66575N, 116.66716W.

occurrenceRemarks.x: Pretty level, open forest of Pinus jeffreyi. Heavy cattle area. Blue bird boxes on some of the trees, and old forest service signs on some trees, designating some dead trees left standing for wildlife use. Some areas had heavy pine duff on ground. But this area had more open sandy floor. Old signs of vehicle tire marks within sand at this site too. Associated species include: Artemisia tridentata, Astragalus douglasii parishii, Penstemon centranthifolius, Aristida divaricata, Bromus tectorum, Abronia villosa aurita, Ericameria pinifolia, Eriogonum evanidum, E. gracile, E. gracile incultum, E. wrightii membranaceum, Lessingia glandulifera, Eriastrum sapphirinum, Cryptantha intermedia, and Heterotheca sessiliflora fastigiata sanjacintensis.
locality.x: San Bernardino National ForestGarner Valley. West side of, and close to Highway 74. Around 1/4 mile north from Ramona trailhead parking area.; Idyllwild 7.5 Quad.
